The AW Conqueror Didot typeface is not inspired by the Didot dynasty of the early 19th century but rather the spectacular interpretations of them appearing in the 1960s and 70s. Decades in which large type sizes were all the rage in advertising and publishing, contrasted typefaces were everywhere. This new font is an ode to the heyday of dry-transfer alphabets and Herb Lubalin, the typographer who mastered the \u2018 tight but not touching\u2019 art of glyphs set ascloseasthis without overlapping.

Le AW Conqueror Didot ne s\u2019 inspire pas des caract\u00E8 res cr\u00E9 \u00E9 s par la dynastie Didot au d\u00E9 but du XIXe si\u00E8 cle, mais plut\u00F4 t des interpr\u00E9 tations spectaculaires apparues dans les ann\u00E9 es 1960 et 1970. Ces deux d\u00E9 cennies voient l\u2019 \u00E9 mergence de compositions typographiques employant des caract\u00E8 res \u00E0 fort contraste en tr\u00E8 s grand corps, notamment dans la publicit\u00E9 et l\u2019 \u00E9 dition. Cette nouvelle fonte fait r\u00E9 f\u00E9 rence \u00E0 l\u2019 \u00E2 ge d\u2019 or des caract\u00E8 res en planche transfert et \u00E0 Herb Lubalin, typographe pass\u00E9 ma\u00EE tre dans l\u2019 art du titrage \u00AB \u00A0 Tight but not touching\u00A0 \u00BB , c\u2019 est-\u00E0 -dire en approches serr\u00E9 es sans chevauchements.
